OL,6,FOne couple received threats from
OL,7,FRichardson through text messages when
OL,8,Fthey failed to make repayments.
OL,10,FThey received benefits and were unable
OL,11,Fto work due to their health
OL,12,Fconditions, but their loan repayments
OL,13,Fgot to the point where they were
OL,14,Fpaying back more than their monthly
OL,15,Fincome, at #1,400 a month.JWhen they
OL,16,Fmissed payments, Richardson texted the
OL,17,Fmale victim saying "Just ring me, you
OL,18,Fknow I can find you" and "You have got
OL,19,Fto speak to me and let me know what's
OL,20,Fgoing on before I come looking for
OL,21,Fyou".
