OL,6,FRichardson was interviewed under
OL,7,Fcaution in November last year and said
OL,8,Fshe had been legally employed as a
OL,9,Fmoney lender since the late 1970s but
OL,10,Fadmitted lending money illegally since
OL,11,F2016.
OL,13,FShe claimed people approached her to
OL,14,Flend money with loan repayments made
OL,15,Fin cash and she kept records.JShe
OL,16,Flater pleaded guilty to engaging in
OL,17,Factivity requiring a licence when not
OL,18,Fa licensee, carrying on a regulated
OL,19,Factivity when not an authorised/exempt
OL,20,Fperson and money laundering.
